reporting-org.narrative: The Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria

title.narrative: To reduce HIV infections by 75%, new HIV infections among children by <5%, AIDS related deaths by 70% and Stigma and Discrimination to 13.8%, all by 2023. To reduce the tuberculosis epidemic and burden by 50% incidence rate and 75% in deaths by 2025.

description.narrative: Tanzania (United Republic) - TB/HIV - Amref Health Africa - Amref. This program has the following goals: To reduce new HIV infections by 75% in 2020, and by 85% in 2023. To reduce new HIV infections among children to less than 5% by 2023. To reduce AIDS related deaths by 50% in 2020 and 70% by end of 2023. To reduce the tuberculosis epidemic and burden by 50% in incidence rate and 75% in deaths by 2025 (from 2015 baseline). The objectives of this program are: To implement efficient testing strategies so that 95% of people living with HIV will know their status by 2022. To reduce the percentage of mother to child transmission at the end of breast feeding period, from an estimated 8% (in 2015), to 4% by the end of 2023. To increase TB treatment coverage from 53% in 2018 to 90% in 2025 by innovatively addressing barriers to access, utilization and the needs of the key and vulnerable populations for TB care and prevention services.
